  <compounddef id="dc/d0f/group___h_a_l___a_d_c" kind="group">
    <compoundname>HAL_ADC</compoundname>
    <title>ADC HAL (ATmega32A)</title>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Implementation notes for analog sampling and conversions. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<sect1 id="dc/d0f/group___h_a_l___a_d_c_1hal_adc_overview">
<title>Overview</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>10-bit ADC with VCC reference (default) and prescaler for 125 kHz clock.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Provides blocking and non-blocking conversions and utility conversions (raw→voltage, raw→power, raw→frequency) aligned to <ref refid="d4/d7e/system__config_8h" kindref="compound">system_config.h</ref> constants.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dc/d0f/group___h_a_l___a_d_c_1hal_adc_cal">
<title>Calibration</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Supports calibration factor to correct for reference/component tolerances.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Allow 2 ms settling after reference changes.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dc/d0f/group___h_a_l___a_d_c_1hal_adc_safety">
<title>Safety &amp; Performance</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Validate channels and pointers; time out if conversion exceeds 1 ms.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Avoids floating point in ISR paths; uses integer math where practical.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
